This paper deals with the application of network slicing for vehicular networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI) and information theory (IT). The proposed method also involves the use of relaying to improve performance, which falls under the category of systems and control (SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the exchange of safety messages and video streaming, which are related to cryptography and security (CR) and multimedia (MM), respectively.
